Company Description: Consol Energy, Through Its Subsidiaries, Is A Producer Of Bituminous Coal IN The United States, With Nearly 20 Bituminous Coal Mining Complexes IN Several States. The Company Produces Both High-Btu Coal And Gas, Which Fuels Approximately Two-Thirds Of All U.S. Power Generation From Reserves Located Mainly East Of The Mississippi River. Consol Energy Is A Major Fuel Supplier To The Electric Power Industry IN The Northeast Quadrant Of The United States. J. Brett Harvey Has Been The Chief Executive Officer Of Consol Energy For More Than Eight Years. He Has Been With The Raw Materials Company For Over Eight Years. Harvey Earned A Bsme Degree From The University Of Utah. Consol Energy Is Based IN Pittsburgh.

Company Description: Exelon Generation, A Division Of Exelon Corporation, Owns And Controls One Of The Largest Generation Portfolios IN The Country, Nearly 33 Gigawatts Of Low-Cost Owned And Contracted Generation. It Is Composed Of A Diverse Mix Of Fossil, Hydro, Nuclear And Renewable Generation Facilities. The Division Consists Of Three Operating Businesses. Exelon Power Is Responsible For Managing, Operating And Maintaining The Company S Fossil And Hydroelectric Plants, Consisting Of Nearly 110 Units Capable Of Generating Approximately 8,000 Megawatts Of Electricity. The Units Are Located IN Pennsylvania, Maryland, Illinois, Texas And Massachusetts. Exelon Nuclear Operates A Large Fleet Of Nuclear Generating Stations. Exelon Nuclear S 10 Stations, With 17 Reactors, Represent Approximately 20 Percent Of The United States S Nuclear Industry S Power Capacity And About 3 Percent Of All U.S. Power Generation. Power Team, Responsible For Marketing Exelon Generation S Product, Works To Develop And Deliver Products That Meet Customer Needs. Power Team S Customers Include Municipal Electric Customers And Cooperative- And Investor-Owned Utilities, As Well As Aggregators, Merchant Participants And Major Commodity Trading Houses. Exelon Generation Is Located IN Kennett Square, Pa.

Company Description: F.M. Brown's Sons, Inc. Has Been Serving Reading, PA And Surrounding Communities For Close To A Century. Put Your Trust IN A Company That Cares About Its Customers And Reliably Delivers The Products And Services They Need. He Fuel Division Of F.M. Brown's Sons, Inc. Began From The Vision Of Our Founder George Brown IN 1843. He Started His Legacy With A Water-Powered Grist Mill, Which Is Now A Registered National Historic Landmark On Monocacy Creek IN Pa. The Mill Stands Today As Solid As The Day It Was Built. Franklin M. Brown, George's Son, Directed The Company And Retired IN 1920. His Four Sons Then Formed The F.M. Brown's Sons Partnership, Which Was Incorporated IN 1948. Franklin's Second Son, B. Clay Brown, Moved To Reading IN 1920 And Began The Coal And Feed Business On Lancaster Avenue. Fuel Oil Was Added To Their Line Of Energy Products IN 1947. B. Clay Brown Retired IN 1969 And The Division Grew Under The Management Of C. Merrill Brown. F.M. Brown's Sons, Inc. Currently Maintains Its Strong Foundation With The Leadership Of The Fifth And  Sixth Generation Of Browns. Make Sure You Have The Fuel You Need Throughout The Year With F.M Brown's Sons, Inc.'s Automatic Delivery Service. We Pride Ourselves On Getting Deliveries To Our Customers On Time, Every Time. Don't Put Up With Delivery Delays Any More. Sign Up For A Full-Service Contract And Receive 24-Hour Emergency Service, So You'Ll Be Warm And Toasty Every Single Night. Experience The Warmth Of A Coal Stove. F.M. Brown's Sons, Inc. Is An Authorized Dealer Of High-Quality Heating Equipment, Including Leisure Line Stoker Stoves And Ashland Hand-Fired Stoves. Business Hours Monday - Friday 7:30 Am - 5:00 Pm Saturday 7:30 Am - 12:00 Pm. Coal Yard Hours Monday - Friday 7:30 Am - 4:30 Pm Saturday 7:30 Am - 11:30 Am.

Company Description: Fmc Agricultural Products Group, Also Know As The Crop Solutions Business, A Subsidiary Of Fmc Corporation, Develops, Manufactures, Markets And Distributes A Full-Line Of Insecticides And Herbicides For Use On A Broad Range Of Crops And Pests. The Company S Products Are Designed To Control Pests And Help Farmers Worldwide Maximize Yields. Fmc S Proprietary Branded Agricultural Products Include Aim Herbicide, Capture Insecticide/Miticide And Mustang Max Insecticides. Fmc Agricultural Also Produces And Markets A Line Of Pest Control Products Targeted To The Structural Pest Control, Turf And Ornamental And Home Garden Markets. The Company Has Five Worldwide Operating Groups, Including North America, Asia-Pacific, Europe-Middle East-Africa, Latin America South And Latin America North. Fmc Agricultural Products Group Maintains Its Corporate Headquarters IN Philadelphia, Pa.

Company Description: Fmc Corporation, Established IN 1883, Is A Diversified Chemical Company Serving Agricultural, Industrial And Consumer Markets Globally Through Various Subsidiaries. The Company S Agricultural Products Segment Provides Crop Protection And Pest Control Products, Such As Insecticides And Herbicides. Its Specialty Chemicals Group, Fmc Biopolymer Is One Of The World S Leading Producers Of Alginate, Carrageenan And Microcrystalline Cellulose. IN The Industrial Chemicals Segment, Fmc Alkali Chemicals Offers Natural Soda Ash, Sodium Bicarbonate, Sodium Cyanide, Sodium Sesquicarbonate And Caustic Soda. Fmc Active Oxidants Supplies Persulfate Products, And Produces Peracetic Acid And Other Specialty Oxidants. Fmc Foret, A Chemical Producer, Provides A Wide Range Of Products, Including Hydrogen Peroxide, Peroxygens, Phosphates, Silicates, Zeolites And Sulfur Derivatives. Fmc Corporation Is Headquartered IN Philadelphia.
